specJson.description:
Named-entity recognition (NER) (also known as entity identification, entity chunking and entity extraction) is a subtask of information extraction that seeks to locate and classify named entities mentioned in unstructured text into pre-defined categories such as person names, organizations, locations, medical codes, time expressions, quantities, monetary values, percentages, etc.

This function extracts named entities from given text using a CRF model obtained from the Named Entity Recognition CRF Train function.

Reference

+ https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Named-entity_recognition

md.en: # NER CRF Predict This function extracts named entities from given text using a CRF model obtained from the Named Entity Recognition CRF Train function. ## Description Named-entity recognition (NER) (also known as entity identification, entity chunking and entity extraction) is a subtask of information extraction that seeks to locate and classify named entities mentioned in unstructured text into pre-defined categories such as person names, organizations, locations, medical codes, time expressions, quantities, monetary values, percentages, etc. This function extracts named entities from given text using a CRF model obtained from the Named Entity Recognition CRF Train function. Reference + https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Named-entity_recognition ## Properties ### VA #### INPUT 1. **table***: (Table) Data including text documents. 2. **model***: (Model) Output model from NER CRF Train function. #### OUTPUT 1. **out_table**: (Table) Table including found named entities with their tags. #### PARAMETER 1. **Input Columns***: String column names to apply the named entity recognition. Available input type is string only. 2. **Language**: Language of the text data. 3. **Extraction**: Extraction of items to return. If None, every possible named entity tag will be chosen. 4. **Column Name Prefix**: Prefix for new column names. ### Python #### USAGE ``` ner_crf_predict(table = , model = , input_cols = , language = , extraction_set = , new_col_prefix = ) ``` #### INPUT 1. **table***: (Table) Data including text documents. 2. **model***: (Model) Output model from NER CRF Train function. #### OUTPUT 1. **out_table**: (Table) Table including found named entities with their tags. #### PARAMETER 1. **input_cols***: String column names to apply the named entity recognition. Available input type is string only. * Type: *list[str]* 2. **language**: Language of the text data. * Type: *str* * Default / Range: eng ( eng | kor ) 3. **extraction_set**: Extraction of items to return. If None, every possible named entity tag will be chosen. * Type: *str* 4. **new_col_prefix**: Prefix for new column names. * Type: *str* ## Example ### VA **[Sample Model]** In this tutorial workflow, text_eng data is used to predict named entities. The output model from NER CRF Train function is applied to predict named entity category of each word. The parameter settings used in the function are shown below. ++Parameters++ 1. **Input Columns***: text 2. **Language**: English 3. **Extraction**: None 4. **Column Name Prefix**:named_entity ### Python ``` from brightics.function.textanalytics import ner_crf_predict input_table = inputs[0] input_model = models[0] result = ner_crf_predict(table=input_table, model=input_model, input_cols=['text'], language='eng', new_col_prefix='named_entity', extraction_set=None) output = result['out_table'] ``` In this tutorial workflow, text_eng data is used to predict named entities. The output model from NER CRF Train function is applied to predict named entity category of each word.
